{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775841179821,"sessionID":"ses_2879e34cfffeVEXMbQEUVmsl00","part":{"id":"prt_d7861f87d001MshhsiuMdKicef","messageID":"msg_d7861ef09001HunksFKZR13WZV","sessionID":"ses_2879e34cfffeVEXMbQEUVmsl00","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-fe9f90ea14204ad4bb218cbc505e1d5b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Runtime API\n2: \n3: This package contains the Kubernetes API definitions for the AgentCube runtime resources.\n4: \n5: ## API Group\n6: \n7: - **Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n8: - **Version**: `v1alpha1`\n9: - **Kinds**: `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter`\n10: \n11: ## Types\n12: \n13: ### AgentRuntime\n14: \n15: `AgentRuntime` is a Kubernetes custom resource that defines a sandbox orchestration runtime for managing the lifecycle of agent pods.\n16: \n17: #### Spec\n18: \n19: The `AgentRuntimeSpec` defines the desired state of an AgentRuntime:\n20: \n21: - **PodTemplate** (*SandboxTemplate, required): Template for creating sandbox pods\n22: - **SessionTimeout** (*metav1.Duration, optional): Timeout for idle sessions before cleanup (default: 15m)\n23: - **MaxSessionDuration** (*metav1.Duration, optional): Maximum allowed duration for a session (default: 8h)\n24: \n25: #### Status\n26: \n27: The `AgentRuntimeStatus` defines the observed state of an AgentRuntime:\n28: \n29: - **Conditions** ([]metav1.Condition, optional): List of conditions representing the runtime state\n30: - **ObservedGeneration** (int64, optional): Most recent generation observed by the controller\n31: \n32: ### CodeInterpreter\n33: \n34: `CodeInterpreter` is a Kubernetes custom resource that defines a code execution environment for managing interpreter sandboxes.\n35: \n36: #### Spec\n37: \n38: The `CodeInterpreterSpec` defines the desired state of a CodeInterpreter:\n39: \n40: - **Image** (string, required): Container image for the interpreter (e.g., \"python:3.11-slim\")\n41: - **Runtime** (string, optional): Execution environment type (default: \"python\")\n42:   - Allowed values: `python`, `javascript`, `typescript`, `go`\n43: - **Timeout** (*metav1.Duration, optional): Maximum execution time for code snippets (default: 5m)\n44: - **Resources** (*SandboxContainerResources, optional): Compute resource requirements\n45: - **Env** ([]SandboxEnvVar, optional): Environment variables to inject\n46: - **EnabledPackages** ([]string, optional): Allowed packages for the interpreter\n47: \n48: #### Status\n49: \n50: The `CodeInterpreterStatus` defines the observed state of a CodeInterpreter:\n51: \n52: - **Ready** (bool, optional): Whether the interpreter is ready to execute code\n53: - **Conditions** ([]metav1.Condition, optional): List of conditions representing the interpreter state\n54: - **ObservedGeneration** (int64, optional): Most recent generation observed by the controller\n55: \n56: ### SandboxTemplate\n57: \n58: Defines the template for creating sandbox pods:\n59: \n60: - **Metadata** (*SandboxMetadata, optional): Labels and annotations for the pod\n61: - **Spec** (SandboxPodSpec, required): Pod specification\n62: \n63: ### SandboxPodSpec\n64: \n65: Defines the pod specification for sandbox pods:\n66: \n67: - **Containers** ([]SandboxContainer, required): List of containers in the pod\n68: - **NodeSelector** (map[string]string, optional): Node selection constraints\n69: - **Affinity** (*SandboxAffinity, optional): Pod scheduling constraints\n70: - **Tolerations** ([]SandboxToleration, optional): Pod tolerations\n71: - **ResourceRequirements** (*SandboxResources, optional): Resource requirements for the pod\n72: - **Volumes** ([]SandboxVolume, optional): Pod volumes\n73: \n74: ## Usage\n75: \n76: ### Creating an AgentRuntime\n77: \n78: ```yaml\n79: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n80: kind: AgentRuntime\n81: metadata:\n82:   name: example-runtime\n83:   namespace: default\n84: spec:\n85:   podTemplate:\n86:     spec:\n87:       containers:\n88:       - name: agent\n89:         image: agent:latest\n90:         ports:\n91:         - containerPort: 8080\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ### Creating a CodeInterpreter\n95: \n96: ```yaml\n97: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n98: kind: CodeInterpreter\n99: metadata:\n100:   name: python-interpreter\n101:   namespace: default\n102: spec:\n103:   image: python:3.11-slim\n104:   runtime: python\n105:   timeout: 5m\n106:   resources:\n107:     limits:\n108:       cpu: \"1\"\n109:       memory: \"1Gi\"\n110:     requests:\n111:       cpu: \"250m\"\n112:       memory: \"256Mi\"\n113:   enabledPackages:\n114:   - numpy\n115:   - pandas\n116:   env:\n117:   - name: PYTHON_VERSION\n118:     value: \"3.11\"\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### Using with client-go\n122: \n123: #### Creating an AgentRuntime\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: import (\n127:     \"context\"\n128:     \"time\"\n129: \n130:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n131:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n132:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n133: )\n134: \n135: func createAgentRuntime(clientset *versioned.Clientset) error {\n136:     runtime := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n137:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n138:             Name:      \"example-runtime\",\n139:             Namespace: \"default\",\n140:         },\n141:         Spec: v1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n142:             PodTemplate: &v1alpha1.SandboxTemplate{\n143:                 Spec: v1alpha1.SandboxPodSpec{\n144:                     Containers: []v1alpha1.SandboxContainer{\n145:                         {\n146:                             Name:  \"agent\",\n147:                             Image: \"agent:latest\",\n148:                         },\n149:                     },\n150:                 },\n151:             },\n152:         },\n153:     }\n154: \n155:     _, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(\n156:         context.TODO(),\n157:         runtime,\n158:         metav1.CreateOptions{},\n159:     )\n160:     return err\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: #### Creating a CodeInterpreter\n165: \n166: ```go\n167: import (\n168:     \"context\"\n169:     \"time\"\n170: \n171:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n172:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n173:     metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n174: )\n175: \n176: func createCodeInterpreter(clientset *versioned.Clientset) error {\n177:     timeout := &metav1.Duration{Duration: 5 * time.Minute}\n178: \n179:     interpreter := &v1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{\n180:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n181:             Name:      \"python-interpreter\",\n182:             Namespace: \"default\",\n183:         },\n184:         Spec: v1alpha1.CodeInterpreterSpec{\n185:             Image:   \"python:3.11-slim\",\n186:             Runtime: \"python\",\n187:             Timeout: timeout,\n188:             EnabledPackages: []string{\"numpy\", \"pandas\"},\n189:         },\n190:     }\n191: \n192:     _, err := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Create(\n193:         context.TODO(),\n194:         interpreter,\n195:         metav1.CreateOptions{},\n196:     )\n197:     return err\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ## Testing\n202: \n203: Run the unit tests:\n204: \n205: ```bash\n206: go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...\n207: ```\n208: \n209: The test suite includes:\n210: - AgentRuntime type tests\n211: - CodeInterpreter type tests\n212: - Sandbox configuration tests\n213: - DeepCopy functionality tests\n214: - JSON serialization tests\n215: - Scheme registration tests\n216: \n217: ## CRD Installation\n218: \n219: The CRD YAML files are located at `config/crd/bases/`:\n220: \n221: - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml`\n222: - `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml`\n223: \n224: Install the CRDs:\n225: \n226: ```bash\n227: kubectl apply -f config/crd/bases/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n228: kubectl apply -f config/crd/bases/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n229: ```\n230: \n231: Verify installation:\n232: \n233: ```bash\n234: kubectl get crd agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n235: kubectl get crd codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ## Features\n239: \n240: ### AgentRuntime\n241: \n242: - **Kubernetes-native**: Leverages Kubernetes CRD and controller patterns\n243: - **Type-safe**: Generated Go types for compile-time safety\n244: - **Extensible**: Supports custom pod templates, volumes, and configurations\n245: - **Status tracking**: Built-in conditions for runtime state management\n246: - **Resource management**: Support for resource limits, requests, and scheduling constraints\n247: - **Security**: Full support for security contexts, capabilities, and seccomp profiles\n248: \n249: ### CodeInterpreter\n250: \n251: - **Multi-language support**: Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, and Go runtimes\n252: - **Resource management**: Configurable CPU, memory, and ephemeral storage limits\n253: - **Timeout enforcement**: Maximum execution time for code snippets\n254: - **Package filtering**: Allowed packages for enhanced security\n255: - **Environment injection**: Custom environment variables support\n256: - **Status tracking**: Ready status and conditions for interpreter state\n257: \n258: ## License\n259: \n260: Copyright 2024 Volcano Authors.\n\n(End of file - total 260 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Runtime API\n\nThis package contains the Kubernetes API definitions for the AgentCube runtime resources.\n\n## API Group\n\n- **Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- **Version**: `v1alpha1`\n- **Kinds**: `AgentRuntime`, `CodeInterpreter`\n\n## Types\n\n### AgentRuntime\n\n`AgentRuntime` is a Kubernetes custom resource that defines a sandbox orchestration runtime for managing the lifecycle of agent pods.\n\n#### Spec\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeSpec` defines the desired state of an AgentRuntime:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/README.md","time":{"start":1775841179803,"end":1775841179819}}}}
